[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cyclist, 22, dies after van collision on Llanbradach bypass

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 22-year-old cyclist has died after being hit by a van in the early hours of the morning.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Emergency services were called to the northbound carriageway of the A469 Llanbradach bypass in Caerphilly county at about 02:00 BST on Wednesday.
Gwent Police said the collision involved a white Volkswagen panel van and a cyclist, who was pronounced dead at the scene.
The carriageway is closed with traffic being diverted through Llanbradach.
Officers are appealing for information about the collision.
